Subject:    Which WKS port number to use for FTP?
From:       <a href="?a=95837692300001&r=1&w=2">Rich Wales &lt;wales () UCLA-LOCUS ! ARPA&gt;</a>
Date:       <a href="?l=namedroppers&r=1&w=2&b=198504">1985-04-29 19:43:58</a></font>
[Download RAW <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837667426400&q=mbox">message</a> or <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837667426400&q=raw">body</a>]</b>

Which port would it be better for everyone to list in WKS RRs to indi-
cate FTP capability -- port 20 or port 21?

(FTP uses port 21 for commands, of course, and port 20 for data.)

To me, it would seem more reasonable to list port 21 -- the command port
-- in a WKS RR.  However, the ISIB and ISIF domain servers seem to be
listing port 20 instead.

I suppose it doesn't really matter which port is used, as long as every-
one agrees on the same choice.

-- Rich

